1. System Requirements
===========================
These requirements define what the system should do and how well it should perform.

Functional requirements
===========================
These describe the core features that the system must provide to users.
1. Given a long URL, the service should generate shorter and unique alias for it.
2. when the user hit a short link, the service should redirect to the original link.
3. link will expire after a standard default time span.

Non Functional requirements
=================================
These define the security , performance and reliability aspects of the system.
1. The system should be highly available. This is really important to consider because if the service
goes down, all URL redirection will start failing.
2. URL redirection should happen in real time with minimum latency.
3. shortened links should not be predictable.

